      <div class="research-content">
        <p class="research-number">02</p>

        <h2>Scientific Understanding and Deep Neural Networks</h2>

        <p>
          My research investigates how deep neural networks may contribute
          to scientific understanding even when their internal operations
          cannot be fully interpreted. I am particularly interested in the
          relationship between predictive success, explanation, and justified
          scientific reliance.
        </p>

        <p>
          This work also examines the role of explainable artificial
          intelligence. Rather than assuming that every scientific model must
          be completely transparent, I consider which forms of explanation
          are relevant in particular research contexts and how partial or
          local explanations can support understanding.
        </p>
      </div>

    </article>

    <article class="research-area">

      <div class="research-image research-image-placeholder">
        <span>Research image</span>
