      <div class="research-content">
        <p class="research-number">03</p>

        <h2>Meaning and Large Language Models</h2>

        <p>
          A further area of my research concerns the semantic competence of
          large language models. I examine what it means for a computational
          system to process or represent linguistic meaning, and how this
          question differs from whether such a system possesses human-like
          understanding.
        </p>

        <p>
          My work distinguishes between technical sensitivity to semantic
          information, competence within a norm-governed linguistic practice,
          and the phenomenological aspects often associated with human
          understanding. This distinction helps clarify both the capabilities
          and the limitations of contemporary language models.
        </p>
      </div>

    </article>

